# graphify scan exclusions for this repo. Patterns are fnmatch-based and
# matched against every path segment, so bare names like `bin` catch any
# depth. Run with detect.py patched (see .graphify-patch/README.md) so
# build/ and .github/ are NOT auto-skipped at root.
#
# Folders intentionally kept (do NOT add here): .github, build, docker,
# src, tests, vcpkg-overlay-ports, vcpkg-overlay-triplets.

# --- Generated .NET / native build outputs (graphify does not auto-skip these) ---
bin
obj
artifacts
vcpkg_installed
TestResults
cmake-build-*
build/coverage-baseline.json

# --- Lock / generated config files (huge transitive dep trees, structural noise) ---
packages.lock.json
*.lock.json
CMakeUserPresets.json.example

# --- Vendored / transitional submodules ---
# external/sdl2-cs is retired in Phase 4 by the CppAst generator (per AGENTS.md).
# external/vcpkg is the upstream submodule.
external

# --- IDE / personal state not already caught by graphify's hidden-dir skip ---
*.user
*.DotSettings.user

# --- .github noise: handoff prompts and one-off java-upgrade tooling ---
# Only keep .github/workflows/*.yml (CI/CD topology).
.github/prompts
.github/java-upgrade
.github/actions

# --- Out of scope ---
# Only docs/decisions/ (ADRs) is kept — those are durable architectural
# memory. Everything else under docs/ moves too fast and AGENTS.md already
# summarizes the canonical content. When adding a new top-level docs folder
# or file, decide here whether to graph it or skip it.
docs/_archive
docs/knowledge-base
docs/phases
docs/playbook
docs/reference
docs/research
docs/reviews
docs/README.md
docs/onboarding.md
docs/plan.md
docs/parking-lot.md

# assets/ is project logos only; no semantic content to extract.
assets
